                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/1855: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-17T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. For General Russell.</p>
                <p>Your April 13, noon.</p>
                <p>If you are satisfied with the regularity and constitutionality of Borno’s
                    election, you are authorized to state that this Government will recognize him as
                    having been elected President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
